<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,492,1302,1329]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
“ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[166,303,1302,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helopioides">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,303,1302,1329]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">helopioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1374,1509]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1374,1400]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The species of this group share three features which are represented by their opposite states in the only member of the “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Villa &amp; G. B. Villa" authorityYear="1833" box="[340,426,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[340,426,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Villa &amp; G. B. Villa" authorityYear="1833" box="[528,650,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[528,548,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[564,650,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely: (1) stria 7 as impressed as other medial striae along elytral anterior third; (2) metacoxal basal sulcus extended on lateral third; and (3) sclerite of internal sac of median lobe without spines. All three traits are considered plesiomorphic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
